":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3852,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/27\/surah-ikhlaas-third-quran\/","url_meta":{"origin":35167,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Surat al-Ikhlas worth one-third of Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 27, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri reported: A man heard another man reciting, \"Say, He is Allah, the One,\" (112:1) again and again. The next morning he came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and told him about it, as if he thought it was not enough to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3984,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/sakina-surat-al-kahf\/","url_meta":{"origin":35167,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sakinah: Tranquility descends with Quran recitation","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bara\u2019 ibn \u2018Azib reported: A man was reciting Surat al-Kahf, and an animal became unsettled in his barn. As he looked, there was a mist or a cloud overshadowing him. The man mentioned that to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \"Keep reciting, O you,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes"